  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>LG ice maker service in LA — Craft Ice + standard ice across the InstaView lineup</h2>
    <p>LG's residential ice-maker installed base in LA splits cleanly between two cohorts. Pre-2019 LG refrigerators run standard cube ice makers at the modular-assembly scale we've seen from LG for a decade — ice-maker module with water valve, ejector motor, thermistor, and ice-bin sensor. Post-2019 InstaView Craft Ice cohort adds a dedicated second ice system for spherical ice, with its own auger motor, heater element, and water solenoid. Service approach differs between the two: standard LG ice-maker service is modular-assembly swap-out routine; Craft Ice service is component-level diagnostic because the 4-stage mechanism has specific failure modes that don't map to conventional cube-ice diagnostic.</p>
    <p>Our LA LG service geography tracks the InstaView install base — design-forward remodels in Silver Lake + Los Feliz + Highland Park, mid-luxury upgrades in Studio City + Sherman Oaks + Manhattan Beach + Pasadena, and ultra-luxury Craft Ice specs in Bel Air + Beverly Hills + Pacific Palisades cocktail-kitchen builds where the 2" crystal-clear sphere is a deliberate design choice for home bars. LG parts through authorized US distribution support same-day or 1-day LA-local parts on common service items. Our techs carry LG modular ice maker assemblies + water-inlet valves + LT800P filters on the truck for single-visit resolution on the majority of calls.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LG ice maker failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Craft Ice auger motor failure</h3><p>Highest-frequency Craft Ice-specific fault. Motor swap $320–$480. Craft Ice auger is LG-specific, not interchangeable with standard ice-maker parts.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Standard ice maker not producing</h3><p>Test-mode diagnostic first. Common: water-inlet valve $220–$340; modular ice-maker assembly $280–$420; thermistor $180–$280.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Undersized or slushy ice</h3><p>Fill-timing drift + temperature targeting. Valve service + temperature verification + thermistor $180–$340 total typical.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>LT800P water filter clog</h3><p>6-month replacement routine. Neglected filter reduces ice-fill pressure + affects cube size. Filter $60–$90.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>ER-code diagnostic (ER FF / ER IF / ER dH)</h3><p>LG error-code readout narrows fault. ER IF (ice-maker fan), ER FF (freezer fan), ER dH (defrost heater) — different parts paths.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>InstaView door-panel access on Craft Ice models</h3><p>Service window adds 30-45 minutes vs non-InstaView. Glass panel temporary removal for ice-maker module access.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LG ice maker product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>LRFVC / LRFOC InstaView Craft Ice</h3><p>French-door with Craft Ice spherical ice + standard cube. 2019+ signature LG platform.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>LRFDS standard French-door</h3><p>Dual ice maker (main + small door-side), modular ice-maker assembly, cube ice only.</p></div>
